author: @mpessan
content:
The concert was big, but she used a playback to compensate for her worn-out voice. Although she is iconic, she kinda forced the issue to live up to the fans' expectation. She is a lady now. I was there and what I saw was a Grandma Madonna, surrounded by dancers who had the swing she lost a long time ago. It was choking to push my way through to leave and get to the subway on my way back home. It was not an experience I would recommend to anyone, no matter if it was free for the crowd or not. For me, it was a fabricated concert. If it weren't for the playback to stir that crowd, she would have been booed for her aged voice and lack of swing.
Unlike me, the whole crowd cheered and hit the sky aided by the caipirinhas and caipvodkas sold by sellers among the fans.
